    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Get Started with B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Storefront Details and Metadata\n Set Up Product Data for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Help Buyers Discover Products on Your Storefront\n Price and Sell Products for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Prices for Storefront Products with Price Lists\n Set Up Promotions for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Enable Promotions for Your Storefront\n Best Practices When Creating Promotions for Your Storefront\n Link a Promotion to a Category\n Link a Promotion to a Product\n Link a Promotion to a Custom URL\n Add a Promotion Image from a Content Delivery Network\n Add a Promotion Image from a Static Resource\n Attach a Promotion Image Directly to a Record\n Target a Promotion at Specific Storefront Users\n Open a Document Attachment from a Storefront Promotion\n Localize Promotions for an Internationalized Storefront\n Offer Coupons for Discounts on Storefront Purchases\n Offer Subscriptions for Products on Your Storefront\n Honor Custom Prices Negotiated in a Contract\n Adjust Product Prices Based on Tiered Quantities\n Host a Seller Marketplace on Your Storefront\n Support Buyer Accounts for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Provide a Smooth Path to Purchase for Storefront Buyers\n Customize the Storefront User Experience\n Strategize for Storefront Success\n Deliver Storefront Performance and Security\n Market Templates for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Solution Resources for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nVISUALFORCE B2B COMMERCE\nBest Practices When Creating Promotions for Your Storefront\n\nWhen you set up a promotion, decide where the promotion appears on your storefront and how you specify the source image file for the promotion.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\n\nSalesforce Compatibility\n\nSalesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience for Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\n\n\nB2B Commerce Compatibility\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Winter ’21 (version 4.13)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’20 (version 4.12)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’19 (version 4.11)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’19 (version 4.10)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’18 (version 4.9)\nSupported Pages\n\nTo specify which storefront page the promotion displays on, select one of the following values from the Page Location picklist.\n\nLanding Page\nStorefront's Home page.\nProduct Detail\nProduct Detail page.\nProduct List Page\nProduct List page.\nShopping Cart\nShopping Cart page.\nAll Pages\nAll of these supported pages.\nNOTE The managed package doesn't use the picklist values Category Landing Page, Order Review, or Order Confirmation.\nSupported Locations on a Page\n\nTo specify the area of a page where the promotion displays, select one of the following values from the Location Type picklist.\n\nSplash (1)\nBelow the header and navigation bar, and above the page columns. Valid only on the Home page. For more information, see Show the Splash Widget.\nBanner (2)\nThe top of the main column content in supported two- and three-column page layouts.\nNOTE In your storefront configuration settings, make sure that the Banner module's Enabled configuration is TRUE.\nLeft Nav (3)\nThe left column in supported page layouts.\nRight Nav (4)\nThe right column in supported page layouts.\nNOTE The picklist values Splash Phone and Mobile are compatible only with the classic storefront interface. For new implementations that use the Bootstrap 3 interface, these picklist values aren't supported.\nSupported Devices and Screen Sizes\n\nYour version of B2B Commerce for Visualforce determines which devices support promotions.\n\nVERSION\tSUPPORT\nSummer ’19 (version 4.11) or later\tPromotions created for Bootstrap 3 storefronts display on any device\nSpring ’19 (version 4.10) or earlier\tPromotions created for Bootstrap 3 storefronts display on any device only when Location Type is Splash. For other Location Type values, promotions display only on desktops\nStart Date and End Date\n\nUse the Start Date and End Date fields to set up time-boxed promotions in advance.\n\nImage Sources\n\nYou can reference the source file for a promotion image in several ways:\n\nReference a file from a Content Delivery Network (CDN).\nReference a file from an uploaded static resource.\nAttach a file directly to the promotion record.\n\nLearn more about the pros and cons of each source option.\n\nNOTE The Override Static Resource, Splash Static Resource, and Splash Override Static Resource picklist options aren't used by the managed package.\nImage File Sizes and Dimensions\n\nIf you attach an image file directly to a record or reference a file included in a static resource, Salesforce file size limits apply.\n\nOptimize the dimensions and resolution of your image source files to fit your storefront's theme. For a reference point for your custom theme, set up a storefront with the demo Capricorn Coffee theme. Use your browser's console window to inspect the image dimensions and CSS rules applied to images. You can also download the demo Capricorn Coffee theme.\n\nLink Type\n\nYou can specify whether a promotion links to another page or URL. In the Link section, select one of the following values from the Link Type picklist.\n\nNone\nThe promotion image displays on the storefront, but doesn't link to another page.\nCategory\nThe promotion links to the Product List page for a particular category.\nProduct\nThe promotion links to the Product Detail page for a particular product.\nURL\nThe promotion links to a custom URL.\nCoupon Codes\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce doesn’t provide a way to automatically apply a coupon code when a buyer clicks a promotion. Instead, include a coupon code in the promotion image, which the buyer must then manually enter during checkout.\n\nSEE ALSO\nSource Options for Storefront Media\nShow the Splash Widget\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
